      "detail": "Captive switching cost means migration to alternative systems is effectively impossible without rebuilding the entire capability stack. Classified data entanglement, certified platform integrations, trained cleared personnel, and operational dependencies all compound the cost. The captive cost is measured in years of recertification delay, capability gaps, and direct national security risk. This captivity is the value-layer expression of the locked-in substitutability driven by classification and certification requirements."
    },
    "Exit": {
      "value": "Capability entangled",
      "memo": "Military AI exit is capability-entangled because trained models retain classified learned capability that cannot be cleanly separated, deleted, or returned.",
      "detail": "Capability entangled exit means terminating the arrangement does not and cannot terminate the capability embedded in model weights. Model weights trained on classified operational data retain that knowledge and capability even after all source training data is deleted. This creates unique decommissioning challenges, allied-sharing complications, and proliferation risks during system retirement. Exit in military AI is never clean because the trained capability persists indefinitely within the model weights."
    },
    "Acceptance Basis": {
