      "memo": "Chain of command legitimises deployment; institutional authority substitutes for transparency or market validation.",
      "detail": "Military deployment accepted on the basis of institutional authority and command structure, not the system own transparency or commercial validation. The chain of command provides the legitimacy framework that civilian contexts derive from process or market. Accountability flows through established military hierarchies rather than technical explainability. This means assurance requirements serve command authority rather than public confidence."
